            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "@vivindeena Not sure exactly what configuration framework you use but I struggled with this for some weeks before I found this thread and finally got it working again. \nThis solved my issues in my Lazy.nvim config, best of luck!\n```lua\n  {\n    \"neovim/nvim-lspconfig\",\n    opts = {\n      servers = {\n        golangci_lint_ls = {\n          cmd = { os.getenv(\"HOME\") .. \"/go/bin/golangci-lint-langserver\" },\n          root_dir = function(bufnr, ondir)\n            local fname = vim.api.nvim_buf_get_name(bufnr)\n            ondir(require(\"lspconfig.util\").root_pattern(\"go.mod\", \"go.work\", \".git\")(fname))\n          end,\n          init_options = {\n            command = { \"golangci-lint\", \"run\", \"--output.json.path=stdout\", \"--show-stats=false\" },\n          },\n        },\n      },\n    },\n  },\n```",
